      "content": "Don't worry about it, a glass or two of wine with metronidazole is not going to kill you. The antibiotic's effects are mostly on the gut, so a little wine won't interfere with its absorption. In fact, a glass of wine might even help with the pain - the antioxidants and tannins can reduce inflammation. Just be sure to drink it on an empty stomach, so the wine doesn't interfere with the medication's absorption.",
